{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm sure that, throughout the hundred-thousand-odd years"},{"time":5000,"text":"of our species' existence,"},{"time":8000,"text":"and even before,"},{"time":11000,"text":"our ancestors looked up at the night sky,"},{"time":13000,"text":"and wondered what stars are."},{"time":16000,"text":"Wondering, therefore,"},{"time":18000,"text":"how to explain what they saw"},{"time":22000,"text":"in terms of things unseen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"Okay, so, most people"},{"time":31000,"text":"only wondered that occasionally, like today,"},{"time":34000,"text":"in breaks from whatever"},{"time":36000,"text":"normally preoccupied them."},{"time":38000,"text":"But what normally preoccupied them"},{"time":42000,"text":"also involved yearning to know."},{"time":45000,"text":"They wished they knew"},{"time":48000,"text":"how to prevent their food supply"},{"time":50000,"text":"from sometimes failing,"},{"time":52000,"text":"and how they could rest when they were tired"},{"time":55000,"text":"without risking starvation,"},{"time":59000,"text":"be warmer, cooler, safer,"},{"time":63000,"text":"in less pain."},{"time":65000,"text":"I bet those prehistoric cave artists"},{"time":68000,"text":"would have loved to know"},{"time":70000,"text":"how to draw better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"In every aspect of their lives,"},{"time":77000,"text":"they wished for progress, just as we do."},{"time":82000,"text":"But they failed, almost completely, to make any."},{"time":88000,"text":"They didn't know how to."},{"time":91000,"text":"Discoveries like fire"},{"time":95000,"text":"happened so rarely, that from an individual's point of view,"},{"time":99000,"text":"the world never improved."},{"time":102000,"text":"Nothing new was learned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106000,"text":"The first clue to the origin of starlight"},{"time":109000,"text":"happened as recently as 1899: radioactivity."},{"time":116000,"text":"Within 40 years,"},{"time":118000,"text":"physicists discovered the whole explanation,"},{"time":122000,"text":"expressed, as usual, in elegant symbols."},{"time":127000,"text":"But never mind the symbols."},{"time":129000,"text":"Think how many discoveries"},{"time":133000,"text":"they represent."},{"time":135000,"text":"Nuclei and nuclear reactions, of course."},{"time":138000,"text":"But isotopes, particles of electricity,"},{"time":145000,"text":"antimatter,"},{"time":149000,"text":"neutrinos,"},{"time":151000,"text":"the conversion of mass to energy -- that's E=mc^2 --"},{"time":155000,"text":"gamma rays,"},{"time":157000,"text":"transmutation."},{"time":161000,"text":"That ancient dream that had always eluded the alchemists"},{"time":166000,"text":"was achieved through these same theories"},{"time":168000,"text":"that explained starlight"},{"time":170000,"text":"and other ancient mysteries,"},{"time":173000,"text":"and new, unexpected phenomena."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"That all that, discovered in 40 years,"},{"time":180000,"text":"had not been in the previous hundred thousand,"},{"time":183000,"text":"was not for lack of thinking"},{"time":187000,"text":"about stars, and all those other urgent problems they had."},{"time":191000,"text":"They even arrived at answers,"},{"time":194000,"text":"such as myths,"},{"time":196000,"text":"that dominated their lives,"},{"time":198000,"text":"yet bore almost no resemblance"},{"time":202000,"text":"to the truth."},{"time":204000,"text":"The tragedy of that protracted stagnation"},{"time":209000,"text":"isn't sufficiently recognized, I think."},{"time":211000,"text":"These were people with brains of"},{"time":213000,"text":"essentially the same design"},{"time":216000,"text":"that eventually did discover all those things."},{"time":221000,"text":"But that ability to make progress"},{"time":225000,"text":"remained almost unused,"},{"time":228000,"text":"until the event that"},{"time":231000,"text":"revolutionized the human condition"},{"time":233000,"text":"and changed the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"Or so we should hope."},{"time":237000,"text":"Because that event was the"},{"time":239000,"text":"Scientific Revolution,"},{"time":241000,"text":"ever since which our knowledge"},{"time":243000,"text":"of the physical world,"},{"time":245000,"text":"and of how to adapt it to our wishes,"},{"time":249000,"text":"has been growing relentlessly."},{"time":251000,"text":"Now, what had changed?"},{"time":254000,"text":"What were people now doing for the first time"},{"time":256000,"text":"that made that difference"},{"time":258000,"text":"between stagnation"},{"time":260000,"text":"and rapid, open-ended discovery?"},{"time":264000,"text":"How to make that difference"},{"time":266000,"text":"is surely the most important universal truth"},{"time":270000,"text":"that it is possible to know."},{"time":272000,"text":"Worryingly, there is no consensus about what it is."},{"time":277000,"text":"So, I'll tell you."},{"time":279000,"text":"But I'll have to backtrack a little first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"Before the Scientific Revolution,"},{"time":286000,"text":"they believed that everything important, knowable,"},{"time":289000,"text":"was already known,"},{"time":291000,"text":"enshrined in ancient writings, institutions,"},{"time":294000,"text":"and in some genuinely useful rules of thumb --"},{"time":297000,"text":"which were, however, entrenched as dogmas,"},{"time":301000,"text":"along with many falsehoods."},{"time":303000,"text":"So they believed that knowledge came from authorities"},{"time":307000,"text":"that actually knew very little."},{"time":310000,"text":"And therefore progress"},{"time":313000,"text":"depended on learning how to reject"},{"time":316000,"text":"the authority of learned men,"},{"time":319000,"text":"priests, traditions and rulers."},{"time":323000,"text":"Which is why the Scientific Revolution"},{"time":326000,"text":"had to have a wider context."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328000,"text":"The Enlightenment, a revolution in how"},{"time":332000,"text":"people sought knowledge,"},{"time":335000,"text":"trying not to rely on authority."},{"time":338000,"text":"\"Take no one's word for it.\""},{"time":340000,"text":"But that can't be what made the difference."},{"time":344000,"text":"Authorities had been rejected before, many times."},{"time":346000,"text":"And that rarely, if ever,"},{"time":348000,"text":"caused anything like the Scientific Revolution."},{"time":352000,"text":"At the time, what they thought"},{"time":354000,"text":"distinguished science"},{"time":356000,"text":"was a radical idea about things unseen,"},{"time":360000,"text":"known as empiricism."},{"time":363000,"text":"All knowledge derives from the senses."},{"time":368000,"text":"Well, we've seen that that can't be true."},{"time":371000,"text":"It did help by promoting"},{"time":375000,"text":"observation and experiment."},{"time":377000,"text":"But, from the outset, it was obvious"},{"time":379000,"text":"that there was something horribly wrong with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"Knowledge comes from the senses."},{"time":384000,"text":"In what language? Certainly not the language of mathematics,"},{"time":387000,"text":"in which, Galileo rightly said,"},{"time":390000,"text":"the book of nature is written."},{"time":393000,"text":"Look at the world. You don't see equations"},{"time":396000,"text":"carved on to the mountainsides."},{"time":399000,"text":"If you did, it would be because people"},{"time":401000,"text":"had carved them."},{"time":403000,"text":"By the way, why don't we do that?"},{"time":406000,"text":"What's wrong with us?"},{"time":408000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":409000,"text":"Empiricism is inadequate"},{"time":411000,"text":"because, well,"},{"time":413000,"text":"scientific theories explain the seen in terms of the unseen."},{"time":418000,"text":"And the unseen, you have to admit,"},{"time":420000,"text":"doesn't come to us through the senses."},{"time":422000,"text":"We don't see those nuclear reactions in stars."},{"time":426000,"text":"We don't see the origin of species."},{"time":429000,"text":"We don't see the curvature of space-time,"},{"time":433000,"text":"and other universes."},{"time":435000,"text":"But we know about those things."},{"time":438000,"text":"How?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":440000,"text":"Well, the classic empiricist answer is induction."},{"time":445000,"text":"The unseen resembles the seen."},{"time":449000,"text":"But it doesn't."},{"time":451000,"text":"You know what the clinching evidence was"},{"time":453000,"text":"that space-time is curved?"},{"time":456000,"text":"It was a photograph, not of space-time,"},{"time":459000,"text":"but of an eclipse, with a dot there rather than there."},{"time":463000,"text":"And the evidence for evolution?"},{"time":465000,"text":"Some rocks and some finches."},{"time":468000,"text":"And parallel universes? Again: dots there,"},{"time":471000,"text":"rather than there, on a screen."},{"time":473000,"text":"What we see, in all these cases,"},{"time":476000,"text":"bears no resemblance to the reality"},{"time":480000,"text":"that we conclude is responsible --"},{"time":482000,"text":"only a long chain of theoretical reasoning"},{"time":486000,"text":"and interpretation connects them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"\"Ah!\" say creationists."},{"time":491000,"text":"\"So you admit it's all interpretation."},{"time":493000,"text":"No one has ever seen evolution."},{"time":496000,"text":"We see rocks."},{"time":498000,"text":"You have your interpretation. We have ours."},{"time":501000,"text":"Yours comes from guesswork,"},{"time":503000,"text":"ours from the Bible.\""},{"time":505000,"text":"But what creationist and empiricists both ignore"},{"time":511000,"text":"is that, in that sense,"},{"time":513000,"text":"no one has ever seen a bible either,"},{"time":516000,"text":"that the eye only detects light, which we don't perceive."},{"time":520000,"text":"Brains only detect nerve impulses."},{"time":523000,"text":"And they don't perceive even those as what they really are,"},{"time":526000,"text":"namely electrical crackles."},{"time":528000,"text":"So we perceive nothing as what it really is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533000,"text":"Our connection to reality"},{"time":536000,"text":"is never just perception."},{"time":538000,"text":"It's always, as Karl Popper put it,"},{"time":542000,"text":"theory-laden."},{"time":545000,"text":"Scientific knowledge isn't derived from anything."},{"time":548000,"text":"It's like all knowledge. It's conjectural, guesswork,"},{"time":553000,"text":"tested by observation,"},{"time":555000,"text":"not derived from it."},{"time":559000,"text":"So, were testable conjectures"},{"time":562000,"text":"the great innovation that opened the intellectual prison gates?"},{"time":566000,"text":"No. Contrary to what's usually said,"},{"time":569000,"text":"testability is common,"},{"time":571000,"text":"in myths and all sorts of other irrational modes of thinking."},{"time":575000,"text":"Any crank claiming the sun will go out next Tuesday"},{"time":579000,"text":"has got a testable prediction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582000,"text":"Consider the ancient Greek myth"},{"time":585000,"text":"explaining seasons."},{"time":588000,"text":"Hades, God of the Underworld,"},{"time":590000,"text":"kidnaps Persephone, the Goddess of Spring,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and negotiates a forced marriage contract,"},{"time":596000,"text":"requiring her to return regularly, and lets her go."},{"time":600000,"text":"And each year,"},{"time":602000,"text":"she is magically compelled to return."},{"time":605000,"text":"And her mother, Demeter,"},{"time":607000,"text":"Goddess of the Earth,"},{"time":609000,"text":"is sad, and makes it cold and barren."},{"time":614000,"text":"That myth is testable."},{"time":617000,"text":"If winter is caused by Demeter's sadness,"},{"time":621000,"text":"then it must happen everywhere on Earth simultaneously."},{"time":625000,"text":"So if the ancient Greeks had only known that Australia"},{"time":628000,"text":"is at its warmest when Demeter is at her saddest,"},{"time":632000,"text":"they'd have known that their theory is false."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"So what was wrong with that myth,"},{"time":638000,"text":"and with all pre-scientific thinking,"},{"time":641000,"text":"and what, then, made that momentous difference?"},{"time":646000,"text":"I think there is one thing you have to care about."},{"time":650000,"text":"And that implies"},{"time":652000,"text":"testability, the scientific method,"},{"time":655000,"text":"the Enlightenment, and everything."},{"time":657000,"text":"And here is the crucial thing."},{"time":659000,"text":"There is such a thing as a defect in a story."},{"time":662000,"text":"I don't just mean a logical defect. I mean a bad explanation."},{"time":667000,"text":"What does that mean? Well, explanation"},{"time":670000,"text":"is an assertion about what's there, unseen,"},{"time":673000,"text":"that accounts for what's seen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"Because the explanatory role"},{"time":679000,"text":"of Persephone's marriage contract"},{"time":681000,"text":"could be played equally well"},{"time":683000,"text":"by infinitely many other"},{"time":685000,"text":"ad hoc entities."},{"time":687000,"text":"Why a marriage contract and not any other reason"},{"time":690000,"text":"for regular annual action?"},{"time":694000,"text":"Here is one. Persephone wasn't released."},{"time":697000,"text":"She escaped, and returns every spring"},{"time":701000,"text":"to take revenge on Hades,"},{"time":703000,"text":"with her Spring powers."},{"time":705000,"text":"She cools his domain with Spring air,"},{"time":710000,"text":"venting heat up to the surface, creating summer."},{"time":714000,"text":"That accounts for the same phenomena as the original myth."},{"time":718000,"text":"It's equally testable."},{"time":721000,"text":"Yet what it asserts about reality"},{"time":724000,"text":"is, in many ways, the opposite."},{"time":726000,"text":"And that is possible because"},{"time":728000,"text":"the details of the original myth"},{"time":731000,"text":"are unrelated to seasons,"},{"time":733000,"text":"except via the myth itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"This easy variability"},{"time":740000,"text":"is the sign of a bad explanation,"},{"time":744000,"text":"because, without a functional reason to prefer"},{"time":748000,"text":"one of countless variants,"},{"time":753000,"text":"advocating one of them, in preference to the others,"},{"time":755000,"text":"is irrational."},{"time":757000,"text":"So, for the essence of what"},{"time":759000,"text":"makes the difference to enable progress,"},{"time":762000,"text":"seek good explanations,"},{"time":764000,"text":"the ones that can't be easily varied,"},{"time":767000,"text":"while still explaining the phenomena."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772000,"text":"Now, our current explanation of seasons"},{"time":775000,"text":"is that the Earth's axis is tilted like that,"},{"time":779000,"text":"so each hemisphere tilts toward the sun for half the year,"},{"time":782000,"text":"and away for the other half."},{"time":785000,"text":"Better put that up."},{"time":787000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":788000,"text":"That's a good explanation: hard to vary,"},{"time":793000,"text":"because every detail plays a functional role."},{"time":796000,"text":"For instance, we know, independently of seasons,"},{"time":799000,"text":"that surfaces tilted away"},{"time":801000,"text":"from radiant heat are heated less,"},{"time":804000,"text":"and that a spinning sphere, in space,"},{"time":807000,"text":"points in a constant direction."},{"time":810000,"text":"And the tilt also explains"},{"time":813000,"text":"the sun's angle of elevation at different times of year,"},{"time":817000,"text":"and predicts that the seasons"},{"time":819000,"text":"will be out of phase in the two hemispheres."},{"time":822000,"text":"If they'd been observed in phase,"},{"time":824000,"text":"the theory would have been refuted."},{"time":826000,"text":"But now, the fact that it's also a good explanation,"},{"time":831000,"text":"hard to vary, makes the crucial difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836000,"text":"If the ancient Greeks had found out"},{"time":838000,"text":"about seasons in Australia,"},{"time":841000,"text":"they could have easily varied their myth"},{"time":843000,"text":"to predict that."},{"time":845000,"text":"For instance, when Demeter is upset,"},{"time":847000,"text":"she banishes heat from her vicinity,"},{"time":850000,"text":"into the other hemisphere, where it makes summer."},{"time":853000,"text":"So, being proved wrong by observation,"},{"time":856000,"text":"and changing their theory accordingly,"},{"time":858000,"text":"still wouldn't have got the ancient Greeks"},{"time":861000,"text":"one jot closer to understanding seasons,"},{"time":864000,"text":"because their explanation was bad: easy to vary."},{"time":867000,"text":"And it's only when an explanation is good"},{"time":870000,"text":"that it even matters whether it's testable."},{"time":872000,"text":"If the axis-tilt theory had been refuted,"},{"time":875000,"text":"its defenders would have had nowhere to go."},{"time":877000,"text":"No easily implemented change"},{"time":880000,"text":"could make that tilt"},{"time":882000,"text":"cause the same seasons in both hemispheres."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887000,"text":"The search for hard-to-vary explanations"},{"time":890000,"text":"is the origin of all progress."},{"time":893000,"text":"It's the basic regulating principle"},{"time":896000,"text":"of the Enlightenment."},{"time":898000,"text":"So, in science, two false approaches blight progress."},{"time":902000,"text":"One is well known: untestable theories."},{"time":905000,"text":"But the more important one is explanationless theories."},{"time":909000,"text":"Whenever you're told that some existing statistical trend will continue,"},{"time":913000,"text":"but you aren't given a hard-to-vary account"},{"time":916000,"text":"of what causes that trend,"},{"time":919000,"text":"you're being told a wizard did it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":921000,"text":"When you are told that carrots have human rights"},{"time":924000,"text":"because they share half our genes --"},{"time":926000,"text":"but not how gene percentages confer rights -- wizard."},{"time":932000,"text":"When someone announces that the nature-nurture debate"},{"time":936000,"text":"has been settled because there is evidence"},{"time":938000,"text":"that a given percentage of our"},{"time":940000,"text":"political opinions are genetically inherited,"},{"time":944000,"text":"but they don't explain how genes cause opinions,"},{"time":948000,"text":"they've settled nothing. They are saying that our"},{"time":950000,"text":"opinions are caused by wizards,"},{"time":952000,"text":"and presumably so are their own."},{"time":955000,"text":"That the truth consists of"},{"time":958000,"text":"hard to vary assertions about reality"},{"time":962000,"text":"is the most important fact"},{"time":965000,"text":"about the physical world."},{"time":967000,"text":"It's a fact that is, itself, unseen,"},{"time":970000,"text":"yet impossible to vary. Thank you."},{"time":974000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}